com.comphenix.attribute

Class NbtFactory.NbtCompound

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<String,Object>
      • com.comphenix.attribute.NbtFactory.NbtCompound
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NbtFactory.Wrapper, Map<String,Object>
    Enclosing class:
    NbtFactory

    public final class NbtFactory.NbtCompound
extends AbstractMap<String,Object>
    Represents a root NBT compound.

    All changes to this map will be reflected in the underlying NBT compound. Values may only be one of the following:

    • Primitive types
    • String
    • NbtFactory.NbtList
    • NbtFactory.NbtCompound

    See also:

    • NbtFactory.createCompound()
    • NbtFactory.fromCompound(Object)
    Author:
    Kristian

      • putPath

        public NbtFactory.NbtCompound putPath(String path,
                                      Object value)
        Set the value of an entry at a given location.

        Every element of the path (except the end) are assumed to be compounds, and will be created if they are missing.

        Parameters:
        path - - the path to the entry.
        value - - the new value of this entry.
        Returns:
        This compound, for chaining.

      • getPath

        public <T> T getPath(String path)
        Retrieve the value of a given entry in the tree.

        Every element of the path (except the end) are assumed to be compounds. The retrieval operation will be cancelled if any of them are missing.

        Parameters:
        path - - path to the entry.
        Returns:
        The value, or NULL if not found.
